The invention will be better understood from a reading of the following detailed description taken in conjunction with the drawing in which like reference designators are used to designate like elements, and in which:


FIG. 1 is a block diagram of an air traffic control (ATC) communications network;


FIG. 2 is a block diagram of an air traffic control (ATC) system in which the voice call group function of the present invention may be implemented;


FIG. 3 is a block diagram of an avionics satellite communication unit in accordance with the invention;


FIG. 4 is a diagram illustrating a TDMA time slice of a communications channel;


FIG. 5 is a diagram illustrating a preferred embodiment digital packet used to carry a digitized voice or digital data message;


FIG. 6 is a flow chart illustrating a preferred embodiment implementation of a "push to talk" function used by members of a voice call group;


FIG. 7 is an example display which may be displayed before a pilot is assigned to a voice call group;


FIG. 8 is an example display screen which may be displayed after a pilot or aircraft has been assigned to a voice call group;


FIG. 9 illustrates a block diagram of satellite communications controller;


FIG. 10 is a block diagram of an ATC system illustrating two different regions of airspace under the control of two different ATC centers;


FIG. 11 is a flow chart of a method for performing a communication handoff;


FIG. 12 is a flow chart illustrating a method of a communication handoff initiated by either the pilot or the avionics satellite communication unit of an aircraft; and


FIG. 13 is a flow chart of a method for determining time based billing costs for utilizing the services of an air traffic controller station.
